      "span_text": "Organic explanations include over 20 ailments, the most convincing being Chagas' disease.  Chagas' disease is endemic in South America, and can be transmitted by the famous great bug of the Pampas, Triatoma infestans, a known carrier of Trypanosoma cruz."
